		<description><![CDATA[Very enlightening post!
I&#039;d always been turned off by maven but now I&#039;m going to give it a closer look.
As an aside, using an xml templating engine like Haml might make editing the pom files
even more palatable.
for eg. in jruby,
%foo
  %bars
     %bar &#039;baz&#039;
Is much more pleasant to work with if you have an xml allergy as I do.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Very enlightening post!<br />
I&#8217;d always been turned off by maven but now I&#8217;m going to give it a closer look.<br />
As an aside, using an xml templating engine like Haml might make editing the pom files<br />
even more palatable.<br />
for eg. in jruby,<br />
%foo<br />
  %bars<br />
     %bar &#8216;baz&#8217;<br />
Is much more pleasant to work with if you have an xml allergy as I do.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
